        "content": "<p>Sorry if this is a bit of noobie question, but how can I get Lean to interpret NNReal as a Set Real? Specifically, I'm trying to get code like this to compile:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Probability</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Moments</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Basic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sq_convex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ConvexOn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NNReal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 556643633,
        "sender_full_name": "Jack McCarthy",
        "timestamp": 1763250105
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You want <code>Set.Ici 0</code></p>",
        "id": 556644318,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1763251078
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's the <code>c</code>losed-<code>i</code>nfinite <code>I</code>nterval with endpoint <code>0</code></p>",
        "id": 556644350,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1763251130
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>actually probably you will need to write <code>Set.Ici (0 : ℝ)</code> since by default you will get the natural number zero</p>",
        "id": 556644531,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1763251319
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks I will try this!</p>",
        "id": 556644878,
        "sender_full_name": "Jack McCarthy",
        "timestamp": 1763251769
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note that NNReal is a type but Ici 0 is a term.</p>",
        "id": 556645936,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1763253115
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Another option is to use <code>ConvexOn NNReal Set.univ (fun x : NNReal =&gt; x ^ 2)</code>.</p>",
